    <item rdf:about="http://flolac.iis.sinica.edu.tw/flolac17/doku.php?id=course:learning&amp;rev=1500949827&amp;do=diff">
        <dc:format>text/html</dc:format>
        <dc:date>2017-07-25T10:30:27+08:00</dc:date>
        <title>course:learning</title>
        <link>http://flolac.iis.sinica.edu.tw/flolac17/doku.php?id=course:learning&amp;rev=1500949827&amp;do=diff</link>
        <description>Automata learning is one type of machine learning algorithm studied since the 70s.
In this lecture, we will cover different types of automata learning algorithms, including the L* algorithm by Dana Angliun, its improved version by Rivest and Shapire, and the tree-based version by Kearns and Vazirani. We will also discuss their applications in system verification.</description>
    </item>
